This is Roberta Manca, the HireSkilling Program Manager at Workfully.

I'm contacting you because your service seems to be exactly what we are looking for.

After getting entry-levels hired in the client company, we conduct a 4-6 week customized and intensive training in live mode with a lead trainer. 
The trainer conducts the lesson part time, and assigns practical tasks for the afternoon, remaining available to the students. 
All this takes place within our platform, which allows uploading all the materials and exercises, as well as evaluating and tracking the participant?s progress. 
The training stage is followed by 3-month technical coaching to support the juniors in their job.

So far we have cooperated with a number of well-known tech companies like Eidosmedia, TravelPerk, The Cocktail, Accenture, etc.  

Currently we want to integrate our platform with infinite quality content so that our trainers can create a customized path for the learners using a diverse content library. 

For this very purpose, we are contacting you because you have exactly that kind of a rich library with high-quality courses that might interest us. So we would like to understand if and how we could possibly integrate your content into our platform. 

If you think there might be a possibility of collaboration, I would be really happy to have a meeting with you  so we can discuss the details. 

Thank you for your attention and I really hope to hear back from you.

Roberta Manca

One of my goals is to increase local research capacity at our sites leveraging online resources given that most of our physicians, students, and learners cannot afford formal degree programs. An idea I have is to curate an online educational curriculum with an in-person component led by my team in partnership with a platform like Coursera in order to build local research capacity. 

Current rates of ~$400/year/learner are probably outside of a scalable solution for our setting (Malawi is one of the poorest countries on Earth). Ideally, we'd start with a pilot program of 5-10 learners and then expand to a larger grant-funded program. 

I'm interested in the lowest possible group rate we could get for 5-10 learners, with a consideration of $0 for one year in anticipation of a grant-funded expansion the following year. Please let me know if there is any interest. Happy to meet by Zoom to discuss. 

Best,
Casey

Hello Coursera how are you?
My name is Daniel and I represent Dazzini Studio. The biggest dubbing studio in Brazil specialized in dubbing for distance graduation and corporate training.
I am writing this email to you because in this new year of 2023 we want to invite you to be part of a new era in the development of our country. In the last 4 years Brazil was governed by a president who had no empathy towards minorities, low-income people or even those who have any disability whether physical, psychological or financial.
Dazzini Studio's main objective is to bring specialized knowledge to the greatest number of people in our country as a way to help rebuild our values through distance education. After 7 years of experience in the business, we have recorded over 5000 hours of audio aimed at the educational and corporate market for companies such as Linkedin, Amazon, Marriott, Microsoft, Burguer King and many others.
What we noticed after doing a lot of market research is that many students often feel unmotivated because a good part of the video material is in a language other than portuguese and, no matter how fluent the student is in the language or can follow the subtitles, the absorption of the content is not as effective as listening in your own language. Not to mention the huge audience that has some visual impairment and only has hearing to learn.
We want Coursera to be part of this story with us.
We know that Coursera is responsible for bringing thousands of students around the world the possibility of developing professionally through its online platforms.
And I can only conclude that we can make history together and change the lives of thousands of brazilians.
Come and get to know a little bit about us and what I propose so that we can work together!
In the videos below I'll talk a little bit about us and show you a little bit of what we are capable of doing!

Daniel Dazzini

1.News Gathering (Crowd Tangle)

4. Social Reporting.

8. Requesting to use Eye witness content
9. Verification of Information
10. Fake News and Misinformation

12. Publishing on Social Media
13. Tips on Operating Independent Media
14. Journalism Ethics

We feel it is important to go through this course because it is important to show the influence the internet has had on Journalism when it comes to Credibility, Ethics, Fake News, Original Content, Content Sourcing & Authority.

As we grow our company we want to work people who we can trust to represent our brand in the best way possible.

We look forward to hearing from you.

Self-Reported Needs:
Dear Coursera team,

This is Purusothman Murasolimaran, a middle class, minority (ethnic Tamil) 20-year-old pre-engineering student from a small town called Kalmunai in Eastern Sri Lanka.


Background


I am studying pre-engineering to mechanical engineering at ESOFT School of Engineering & Higher National Diploma in Computing at ESOFT Metro Campus
https://esoft.lk/school-of-engineering/
under the registration numbers: KTBA001709 & E028069

I would like to continue my academic & professional educational development with Coursera by signing up for & committing to various courses in the platform through the Coursera Plus plan. I have an account under the mail mbruce.edu@gmail.com 

I am aware that Coursera is already providing a fair price for its Plus subscription of 49 USD allowing enthusiastic students like me to attend multiple expensive courses under a reasonable price bracket 

But, the country I am from: Sri Lanka is facing its worst economic crisis in its entire history with all-time high inflation rates up to 61% and exhaustion of forex reserves in 2022 making it incredibly hard for citizens to afford services from outside of Sri Lanka.

As of today the exchange rate is 1 USD = 364.96 LKR making even the reasonably priced subscription monthly plan of 49 USD expensive when converted to local currency aptly, 17, 883 LKR
which is unfortunately unaffordable for a currently unemployed student like me with a maximum monthly income of 20 000 LKR (around 55 USD)
Furthermore, being affected by the Covid-19 pandemic, Sri Lankan political unrest and civil protests of 2022 under an authoritarian regime, x3 folds increase of living expenditure with food inflation as high as 85% and other goods at 51%

even leading a day-to-day life has been a struggle of survival.

I am currently conducting my current education from a considerate sponsorship from a mentor from my previous employment without which I would not be able to finance my studies & my family household income has gone down with my father losing his job which prevents me from being able to afford the Coursera services at this point in time. 




Request


Thus, I am humbly requesting you to please consider offering me a suitable further discount from the Coursera Plus monthly subscription of 49 USD for the next 12 months

or the Coursera Plus annual subscription of 399 USD till I can graduate in 2023, and I pledge to be a customer of Coursera once the offered discounted plan ends & show commitment to my education by completing various courses & promote the service within my existing network.

This will immensely help me out in continuing & receiving quality education from a country where opportunities are scarce, grow me as an individual & in the professional setting & further my life considerably coming from an underserved background

I had already signed up for a free trial and was attending 2 courses on SEO Fundamentals from UC Davis under the Search Engine Optimization (SEO Specialization) & Business Writing from University of Colorado Boulder under Effective Communication: Writing, Design, and Presentation Specialization , 
Both of which I lost access to due to payment failure due to my financial status & Sri Lanka?s restrictions on outward remittance. 


I have attached a photo for verification with my student ID & National Identity Card and you can contact me for further details needed which I will be happy to provide.


To verify authenticity of my student status claim you can mail me on my student email address KTBA001709@esoft.academy

P.S Apologies for contacting on multiple mail handles, I couldn?t find a mail address for scholarships & financial aid on the Coursera page thus, I wrote on multiple avenues. 


Yours Gratefully,

Pendarahan paling banyak biasanya terjadi 4-8 jam setelah menggunakan dosis misoprostol yang pertama dan mulai berkurang dalam 24 jam. Beberapa perempuan mungkin akan melihat gumpalan dalam beberapa hari kedepan atau beberapa minggu, tergantung gumpalan yang dikeluarkan.
Cytotec apakah bahaya?
Cytotec ® tergolong sebagai obat aborsi yang berpotensi membahayakan kehamilan. Obat ini memicu kontraksi serta pendarahan pada rahim. Oleh karena itu, jangan minum obat Cytotec Asli® apabila Anda sedang hamil.

Apakah Perdarahan bisa Menyebabkan Keguguran?
Keguguran adalah kondisi meninggalnya janin di saat umur kehamilan masih di bawah 20 minggu. Keluarnya darah dari vagina adalah salah satu tanda keguguran. Meski demikian, terjadi perdarahan saat hamil bukan berarti Anda pasti mengalami keguguran.
Kenapa Janin Tidak Bisa Digugurkan?
Penyebab pasti dari tidak berkembangnya janin tersebut tidak diketahui. Hal ini diduga dikaitkan oleh kelainan kromosom yang terjadi di dalam sel telur yang dibuahi, hasil dari genetika atau sel telur dan sperma berkualitas rendah dan karena faktor kurangnya dosis yang diberikan saat aborsi, jadi untuk gugurkan kandungan harus sesuaikan dosis / jumlah obat aborsi sesusuai kebutuhan masing-masing janin apabila kandungan anda kuat diharuskan menggunakan paket tuntas 8 bulan yang disarankan dokter hallobunda.store

On behalf of the Anti-Crisis Coordination Headquarters of DTEK, the leading Ukrainian private energy group we would like to thank you for your ongoing support to Ukraine and Ukrainians. 
Over the last 17 years DTEK has been investing in the energy sector of Ukraine and operates assets in thermal power generation, electricity distribution, energy and energy services supply, energy trading, gas production, renewables development and clean tech innovations. Amidst the unjustified war of aggression waged by russia, the society, economy and national defense critically depends on robust and resilient operation of the energy system. Since very first hours of February 24th 2022, DTEK relentlessly contribute to enabling uninterrupted functioning of critical energy infrastructure that has been increasingly targeted and damaged by russia?s missiles and drones shelling as well as by cyber-attacks.

Since 10th of October 2022 the energy facilities operated by DTEK (thermal power generation, coal mines and distribution grids) have been massively targeted by more than 100 russian missiles and drones. This resulted in severe damages to five of DTEK?s power plants as well as electricity distribution system operators managed by the group. The russian military forces targeted the electricity transmission system, power generating plants and other energy facilities as well that resulted in shortages of electricity supplies and rolling blackouts that affects more than 4 million of Ukrainians across the entire country.

The coming winter adds urgency in addressing these challenges taking into consideration that the reliable supply of energy becomes even more crucial to avoiding a humanitarian catastrophe, to maintain military capabilities, to strengthen nation?s capacity to withstand the enemy and to advance the victory of Ukraine. Therefore DTEK relentlessly undertakes a comprehensive set of anti-crisis measures in protecting freedom and sovereignty of the country with our employees demonstrating outstanding courage and dedication at their working places. These anti-crisis measures include finding, delivering and if necessary financing the replacement, restoration and maintenance of the critically needed equipment and elements of energy infrastructure. In doing so the company closely coordinates its actions with the Ministry of Energy of Ukraine and with other Ukrainian energy companies.

In this extraordinary situation of the war and humanitarian crisis looming at the European continent we would sincerely appreciate if you could consider a possibility to provide an opportunity for DTEK IT employees to take courses free of charge during 2023.

We would like to thank you once again for already provided support and we would rely on your understanding and generosity with assessing our request. 
Considering emergency we are facing, we would appreciate if you could share with us with your hopefully positive decision at your earliest convenience. In case you might need any additional information and clarifications from our side please do not hesitate to contact Oleksii Pustovitov (Manager of IT infrastructure department).

Self-Reported Needs:
Dear Sir/Madam,
Thank you for giving us the opportunity to contact you!

We are a team of 7 employees, working for the Hellenic Rescue Team (HRT), a Voluntary Non-Profit Search and Rescue Organization, based in Greece. With over 1.500 volunteers all over our country, HRT supports operations in response to emergencies and mass disasters, wherever they take place, whether in Greece or abroad. 

We offer our services, in collaboration with the Civil Protection authorities, in cases of mountain and sea accidents, wildfires, floods and earthquakes, but we also provide training courses to the community and organize open events, aiming at raising awareness in self-protection and prevention related matters. 
Additionally, we train students, civilians and corporate staff in First Aid. 

For our rescue activities at sea during the major refugee crisis in Greece, our organization was honored in November 2016 with the UNHCR Nansen Refugee Award, which is the highest honor awarded by the UNHCR. The award was offered to our volunteers for supporting over 2.500 people in 1.100 search and rescue operations during dangerous sea crossings and providing safe shelter for the most vulnerable once they reached land.

Most of us are familiar with your services and we strongly believe that through your innovative courses you can support us in strengthening and empowering our skills and knowledge, in order to become more effective and achieve greater social value, sustainability and long-term objectives. The courses that interest us the most are primarily management related, namely project management, marketing, leadership, communication skills and CSR.

We would be very happy if you provided us free access to the above-mentioned courses and, thus, supporting us in further developing our organization and the social impact on civil protection. In terms of reciprocity, our organization will promote your contribution on all our social media platforms.
Thanks once more and we look forward to hearing from you!

Best Regards,

HRT Staff

Iosif Vourvachis
Alexandros Giordanis
Dimitris Iliadis
Meni Kourkouta
Evangelia Temeridou
Sakis Doutsiopoulos
Eleni Gerouda

Campaign Name: Contact Sales - Enterprise Website Learn More
TItle: Sourcing Specialist
Self-Reported Needs:
Dear Supplier,
Greetings from NIIT!

We are approaching you with a requirement from one of our Ultimate Client.

NIIT is being appointed by Ultimate Client as a Managed Service Provider for training requirements. 

We need a solution to upskill Ultimate Client employees with training on Supply Chain Management (After Sales).

Introduction
Competence assessment campaigns and resources reviews show that our population in Airbus commercial Customer Services domain needs to be upskilled in everything related to supply chain management in the frame of Aftersales.
That's why we would like to launch a training to add in our learning offer a set of learning solutions around supply chain management, logistics, inventory management and transport, all customized for the After Sales environment.

As is situation
Competence gaps identified in the business on supply chain management in After Sales (competence assessment campaigns + resources reviews).

Languages
French; English; German; Spanish

Expected situation
Business upskilled and driving efficient supply chain management activities

Learning objectives

1/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON GENERAL CONTEXT OF SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT IN AFTER SALES 
a. Understand that effective supply chain management is critical to ensure the availability of spare parts, timely delivery of maintenance and repair services, and overall customer satisfaction. 
b. Be aware that effective supply chain management involves managing inventory levels, optimizing logistics and transportation, ensuring quality control and leveraging technology to improve efficiency and visibility throughout the supply chain.
Target proficiency levels: basic

2/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT IN AFTER SALES
a. Understand that Supply chain is governed by just-in-time processes, reduced repair cycles and after-sales performance commitments. 
b. Have an end to end view of the supply chain in after sales for the aeronautics industry: flow of goods, services and information from the manufacturer of aviation equipment and components to the customers. This includes managing the various activities involved in the delivery of spares parts, maintenance, repair and overhaul services, as well as managing the relationships with suppliers, distributors and service providers.
Target proficiency levels: basic

3/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON LOGISTICS IN AFTER SALES
 Understand the importance of managing Logistics effectively, with a dedicated focus on the After Sales environment. 
Target proficiency levels: autonomous, advanced

4/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON INVENTORY MANAGEMENT IN AFTER SALES
a. Understand the added value of efficiently managing the stock of spare parts and components required for maintenance, repair and overhaul (MRO) activities and be aware of its impact on the overall customer satisfaction.
b. Understand the need to maintain optimal inventory levels while minimizing excess stock and avoiding stockouts: this involves forecasting demand for spare parts, identifying critical components, tracking inventory levels and strategies to ensure the timely availability of parts.
c. Inventory analytics (theoretical & practical knowledge)  
Target proficiency levels: autonomous, advanced  

5/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON TRANSPORT IN AFTER SALES
 a. Understand that transport is critical to the success of the after sales market, and that effective management of transportation can improve efficiency, reduce costs and enhance customer satisfaction. Understanding of different transport models (3PL/4PL).
 b. Transport in aftersales process: process mapping, analysis of workflows, process    efficiency measurement.
 c. Be aware of the stakes of transportation in the after sales market: 
- timeliness: timely transportation of parts and components is essential to minimize AOG, delays in transportation can affect customer satisfaction and revenue
- safety: transportation of parts and components must be handled with the utmost care to prevent damage, loss or theft. Special attention to safety regulations and procedures is needed.
- cost: what are the transportation costs impacts? highlight the need of optimizing routes, using the appropriate transportation modes and leveraging technology to improve transportation efficiency
- globalization: transportation includes crossing borders, dealing with customs regulations and complying with international laws and standards.
Target proficiency levels: autonomous, advanced  

6/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON DIGITIZATION IN SUPPLY CHAIN
a.understanding how and ensuring that different supply chain tools work together to optimize process integration, bringing accurate data and processes together under one unified platform to provide end-to-end visibility
b.get to know different digitization techniques and tools
c.know and understand the stages of supply chain digitization
Target proficiency levels: basic, autonomous, advanced  

7/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON SUPPLY CHAIN SUSTAINABILITY
a.Understand why sustainability is important in supply chain management (improve productivity while saving money at the same time. By using sustainable techniques and resources, you increase the efficiency of buildings, vehicles and machinery at a significant cost savings)
b.consider the environmental and human impact of the products' journey through the supply chain (from raw materials sourcing to production, storage, delivery and transportation)
Target proficiency levels: basic, autonomous, advanced  
8/ LEARNING SOLUTION(S) ON SUPPLIER DEVELOPMENT & MANAGEMENT IN AFTERMARKET CONTEXT
a.Supplier performance Monitoring : Understand the principles of monitoring supplier performance and the use of the different indicators to ensure suppliers meet the contractual and performance obligations (whether for MRO, logistics or warehouse providers)Understand how to steer, control and monitor supplier performance in aftermarket - assessing supplier performance, defining and setting expectations for quality and delivery, and maintaining relationships Know the basis of supplier relationship management (incl. supplier strategy,  managing vendor deliverables, working collaboratively to co-develop new processes, managing compliance as well as payment of invoices, ...) 
b.Supplier's excellence: How to ensure that suppliers meet or exceed Airbus Customer Services expectations in terms of quality, delivery, and cost.

Learning Format
Online; Classroom; Virtual classroom; Blended

Target Population
Customer Services employees in Airbus commercial, especially those dealing with Supply Chain topics (mainly white collars in SO, SM and Satair)

Number of Learners
2023: 50 to 100p expected. 2024: 50 to 100p expected.

Trainees level of expertise
Heterogeneous levels.
Most of them have basic level (especially on new topics like Supply Chain digitization or Supply Chain sustainability) or autonomous levels.
We would also need some advanced level trainings to develop our experts, in particular providing them with best practices from other companies.

We look forward to working with you to fulfill Ultimate Client's training requirements, please feel free to write me for any clarification required.

Regards,
Vikas Beniwal
On behalf of NIIT Ltd.
Subcontractor for Airbus Develop ? HU
Email: Airbus.Learning-vendor@niit.com

Yash vasandani

Self-Reported Needs:
Hi there,

We are reaching out regarding a possible sponsorship for Online Monmouth Math Competition (OMMC). OMMC is a 501(c)(3) accredited student-led nonprofit focusing on accessible math education. OMMC is planning its 3rd annual math competition, and we need financial support to make it a reality. The competition will be held virtually from May 12th to May 29th. 

Our community platform on Discord currently consists of around 3000 students, growing into one of the largest online communities for competitive math. Just last year, we received over 100 teams for OMMC 2022. 

I personally find Coursera's expansive curriculum and mission to provide free educational resources to learners everywhere very important, and with OMMC I would like to expand this vision to encompass the field of competitive math. If you are interested in supporting OMMC's similar mission of providing free competitive math resources, networks, and platforms to middle and high school students around the world, we would appreciate any stipend or monetary grant that Coursera could provide to help run our website, fund community events, and offer prizes to our top-performing competitors.

As one of our sponsors, we will credit you on our website and promote materials of your choosing through our online platforms (Discord, Instagram, and Youtube), and on all of our merchandise (T-shirts, hoodies, etc.), connecting your organization to thousands of interested students around the world. 

If you would like to know more about OMMC, please check out our website: http://www.ommcofficial.org/. We are willing to answer any other questions you may have.

Thank you very much for your time and consideration, 
Ishaan Akula
Co-Founder & Director, OMMC

Self-Reported Needs:
Dear Coursera,

I hope this email finds you well. My name is Krishna, and I am reaching out to introduce myself and offer my custom letter writing services to your students with a profit-sharing arrangement.

As a skilled writer with experience in various industries, I specialize in crafting personalized, professional letters that can help your students communicate more effectively with their peers, professors, and potential employers. Whether they need to write a cover letter, an application essay, or a thank-you note, I can help them create letters that showcase their strengths, goals, and unique voice.

I understand that writing custom letters can be a challenging task, especially for students who are juggling multiple responsibilities and deadlines. That's why I offer a range of services to meet their specific needs, including:

Custom letter writing
Editing and proofreading
Feedback and revision support
Template creation and customization

What's more, I am pleased to offer a profit-sharing arrangement for your students. For every letter I write for them, I will donate a portion of my fee to your institution, which you can allocate to support student programs, scholarships, or other initiatives. This is a win-win opportunity for your students to receive high-quality writing services and contribute to the success of your institution.

To make the process as seamless as possible, I can send the completed letter to you for review and approval before forwarding it to the student. This ensures that the letter meets your institution's standards and that your students receive timely and accurate feedback.

My rates are affordable and flexible, and I am committed to delivering high-quality work that meets your students' requirements and exceeds their expectations. I believe that effective communication is crucial to the success of any student, and I am passionate about helping them achieve their academic and career goals through clear and compelling writing.

I would be happy to provide samples of my work and discuss how my services can benefit your students and institution. If you are interested in learning more, please don't hesitate to reply to this email.

Thank you for your time and consideration, and I look forward to the opportunity to work with you.

Best regards,
Krishna
Representative of The Skilled Touch

Since we are a small refugee-led NGO which started in 2020, we have limited resources, however, we are dedicated to improving and expanding. Therefore, I am reaching out to you now. Our organisation would be interested in improving its staff's skills to advance the quality of our work and thus support our fight against human rights violations in education. The respectable Coursera platform would be the right place to do this, as it provides multiple high-quality courses in the field of human rights that can be relevant to our organisation.

As I mentioned earlier, our financial means are limited, thus I would like to ask whether you would be willing to kindly discuss a discount or a couple of free spots for one or some of the courses your platform provides.

If you are open to having a conversation on this and your capacity allows it, we would be pleased to have an online meeting with you. However, if that is not possible, we are more than happy to give some further details in an email about our goals, needs, and what we could potentially offer Coursera to compensate for a potential discount.  

Thank you for your time and consideration! Looking forward to hearing from you at your convenience.

Kind regards,

Johanna Farkas

The Spivdiia.org.ua team

Self-Reported Needs:
As you may know, traditional payment methods such as credit cards and PayPal are not widely used in our country (Libya), and this can make it difficult for some users to access the valuable courses on your platform. However, we have a solution to this issue. We are a partner with a reputable aggregator company that provides Direct Carrier Billing (DCB) services to the local market. With their service, users can easily and securely pay for purchases using their mobile credit balance. This payment method is highly popular and widely used in our country, and we believe it would be an ideal solution for users who want to access your courses.
We would like to propose that Coursera consider enabling mobile credit payments for users in Libya, leveraging our partnership with the aggregator company. This would allow more users to access the high-quality courses on your platform, and create new opportunities for growth in our local market.
By partnering with Coursera, we believe we can bring even more value to our users by offering them access to Coursera's extensive course library, while also providing a seamless payment experience through our aggregator company's DCB service.
We believe that this partnership could be mutually beneficial, and we would be happy to discuss the details further. Thank you for your time and consideration.

TItle: Senior Finance Officer
Self-Reported Needs:
As a finance officer, we would typically be required to work extensively with spreadsheets and financial data using Microsoft Excel. Here are some advanced Excel skills that can be particularly useful for finance officers:

Financial Modeling: we should be able to create financial models that can analyze and forecast data, generate charts, and conduct sensitivity analysis.

Advanced Functions and Formulas: we should be proficient in advanced Excel functions such as VLOOKUP, HLOOKUP, SUMIF, COUNTIF, INDEX, MATCH, and OFFSET, among others. These functions can help you automate tasks, analyze large data sets, and improve your productivity.

Pivot Tables and Charts: we should know how to use Pivot Tables and Pivot Charts to summarize and analyze complex data. You can create dashboards, reports, and other visualizations using these tools.

Macros and VBA: We should have a basic understanding of macros and Visual Basic for Applications (VBA) to automate repetitive tasks, generate customized reports, and enhance your efficiency.

Data Analysis: we should have strong data analysis skills and be familiar with statistical tools and techniques, such as regression analysis, correlation analysis, and hypothesis testing.

Data Visualization: We should know how to use Excel to create interactive and visually appealing charts, graphs, and other visualizations that can help you communicate your findings and insights to others.

These are just some of the advanced Excel skills that finance officers should have to be successful in their roles

Campaign Name: Contact Sales - Enterprise Website Learn More
Self-Reported Needs:
To whom it may concern,


I am writing to you on behalf of the McGill University Chapter of Engineers in Action (MEIA).  We are a student-run club committed to taking action to improve the living conditions of impoverished people and raise global awareness among students. Our main goal is to construct footbridges that provide year-round safe access to essential health care, education, and economic opportunities and services to the rural communities in developing countries. It is through the design and construction of pedestrian bridges that we seek to provide safe access to these resources throughout the year, especially during flood season. In summer 2021, we will send volunteer students to Africa in partnership with University of Colorado Boulder, to build a footbridge. 


In order to accomplish this, the McGill chapter of EIA intends to finance the bridge project costs, as well as the travel and living expenses of our volunteers through various activities. Therefore, we, McGill EIA Chapter, humbly request your support. For more information, please see the attached sponsorship package.


Please feel free to visit the EIA Bridge Program website, our Facebook page for pictures from our recent eSwatini Bridge Project. 


Lastly, please contact me if you see a potential partnership between Coursera and McGill Engineers in Action.


Regards, 

Thomas Jogand-Coulomb
VP Sponsorship EIA
vpsponsorship.eia@mcgilleus.ca

The partnership will, therefore, help the foundation to reach more individuals and communities, and provide them with the education they need to thrive.

Overall, the partnership between the Sydney Mabitla Foundation and Coursera is a valuable initiative that aims to provide underprivileged individuals in South Africa with access to quality education and the opportunity to improve their lives.
